The students should understand the basic significance of dentistry of the stomatognatic system.
The students should be familiar with the physiologic function and pathophysiologic mechanisms of the stomatognatic system.
The students should know and understand the relationship between the temporomandibular joints, the movements of the lower jaw and the teeth.
The students should be able to diagnose and treat temporomandibular TMD.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The main aim of the course is to integrate different disciplines such as the anatomy, physiology, restaurative dentistry, prosthetic dentistry, orthodontics, oral and maxillofacial surgery and radiology into the multidisciplinary field of stomatognatic physiology.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Stomatognatic physiology is a basic discipline of dental science. A well-functioning stomatognatic system should be the goal of all dental treatment. The students should be familar with the functions of stomatognatic physiology and patopfysiological mechanisms. Students should understand the connections between temporomandibular joints and surroudings tissues. Students should be able to perform the TMJ clinical examination, to diagnose and suggest treatment.
